edu.kit.scc.dem.wapsrv.controller

Class WapPathMatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.kit.scc.dem.wapsrv.controller.WapPathMatcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.util.PathMatcher

    public class WapPathMatcher
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.springframework.util.PathMatcher
    This implementation of a PathMatcher introduces patterns needed for implementation of the WAP server. The usual logic defines fixed endpoint URLs, which get varying data via fixed parts of their URL, request parameters or via HTML headers or bodies. In our case, we have varying endpoints, and decisions cannot be made using the default tools provided by spring without being left with only one endpoint per HTPP-request type. Only requests matched against the new patterns defined here will be intercepted, everything else gets delegated to the spring default implementation of PathMatcher.

    Usage examples that also show how to distinguish between page and container:
    Container : \@RequestMapping(value = WapPathMatcher.CONTAINER_AND_PAGE_PATTERN, method = RequestMethod.GET)
    Page : \@RequestMapping(value = WapPathMatcher.CONTAINER_AND_PAGE_PATTERN, params = {"iris","page"}, method = RequestMethod.GET)

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Matthias Dressel, Michael Hitzker, Markus Hoefler, Andreas Loeffler, Timo Schmidt
